  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Embracing math in the mexican youth, mainly girls</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mexican Youth ranked 53rd out of 65 OECD countries participating in the Programme for International Student Assessment (PISA) 2018 study.  Boys outperformed girls in mathematics by 12 points, a larger gap than the average gender gap in math in OECD countries: 5 points. Mexican girls significantly outperformed boys in reading; the gender gap was 11 points.  We must enable them to have better academic results and foster their mental health. We can detect and correct learning difficulties.</narrative>
  </description>
